The paper deals with video summarization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of memory networks is a key aspect of the proposed model, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of selecting relevant subshots for summarization. Finally, the evaluation of the model's performance involves machine learning (cs.LG).
